Private equity firm General Atlantic
LLC agreed to pay 1.2 billion reais ($561.8 million) for a 30
percent stake in Brazilian brokerage XP Investimentos CCTVM SA,
Veja reported, without saying where it got the information.  Guilherme Benchimol and Marcelo Maisonnave remain as
controlling shareholders, Veja said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
